The issue was caused by the `IndentationRule` incorrectly calculating the expected indentation for lambda parameters when the lambda is part of a function call that spans multiple lines. Specifically, the rule was calculating the indentation based on the length of the text preceding the lambda on the *start of the function call*, rather than aligning with the start of the lambda block itself (or the first parameter's line) when using IntelliJ IDEA default formatting.

When `ktlint_official` code style is not used (e.g., `intellij_idea`), the rule attempts to mimic IntelliJ's behavior. The previous implementation assumed that the text before the lambda was on the same line as the start of the call expression, which led to incorrect indentation calculations (expecting 18 spaces instead of 12 in the reproduction case) when arguments were wrapped.

I fixed this by modifying `calculateIndentOfFunctionLiteralParameters` in `IndentationRule.kt`. The new implementation:
1.  Locates the first value parameter of the lambda.
2.  Calculates the visual column of this parameter relative to the start of its line.
3.  Determines the required indentation offset relative to the current block indentation.

This ensures that subsequent parameters are aligned with the first parameter, matching the visual structure of the code and complying with IntelliJ's default formatting behavior for lambdas.

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case in `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/IndentationRuleReproductionTest.kt` which confirmed the issue (failed with expected violation) and then passed after the fix. I also ran existing tests (`IndentationRuleTest` and `ParameterListWrappingRuleTest`) to ensure no regressions were introduced.

Relevant code changes in `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/IndentationRule.kt`:
```kotlin
        } else {
            // Allow default IntelliJ IDEA formatting:
            // val fieldExample =
            //     LongNameClass { paramA,
            //                     paramB,
            //                     paramC ->
            //         ClassB(paramA, paramB, paramC)
            //     }
            val firstValueParameter =
                treeParent
                    .findChildByType(VALUE_PARAMETER_LIST)
                    ?.findChildByType(VALUE_PARAMETER)
            if (firstValueParameter != null) {
                val column = firstValueParameter.columnOnLine()
                val indent = column - currentIndent().length
                if (indent >= 0) {
                    " ".repeat(indent)
                } else {
                    indentConfig.indent.repeat(2)
                }
            } else {
                indentConfig.indent.repeat(2)
            }
        }
```
And added `columnOnLine` helper method.

